ROM PATCHER ALLOWS YOU TO MODIFYPART OFTHE APPLE'S ROM CODE; COPYROM INTO RAM;AND THEN CONTINUE TORUN WITH THE RAM   VERSION INCONTROL.  ONE APPLICATION    WOULDBE TO CHANGE A KEYWORD OR ERRORMESSAGE; WHOSE ADDRESSES AREREVEALED BYTHE 'ROM KEYWORD DUMP'PROGRAM.  THIS   WORKS UNDER DOS 3.3ONLY.  TO USE IT; ATTHE PROMPT TYPEIN THE MONITOR STRINGTHAT IS USED TO ALTER MEMORY (OTHERMONITOR COMMANDS WORK AS WELL).  FOREXAMPLE; TRY THE FOLLOWING:D270:4E 49 42 42 4C C5 N D1CC:41 494ETHIS WILL CHANGE 'SYNTAX ERROR' TOSOMETHING MORE FAMILIAR; AND WILLCHANGETHE 'PRINT' STATEMENT TO'PAINT'.REMEMBER; ALL MODIFICATIONS YOU MAKETO THE ROM CODE WILL DISAPPEAR WHENYOU    PRESS CTRL-RESET OR WHEN YOUPOWER DOWN.